cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper is about adapting the Resilient Propagation (Rprop) algorithm for deep learning, specifically for training deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of the modified Rprop algorithm for improving learning speed and accuracy, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper applies the method to the MNIST dataset, which is a common dataset used in computer vision tasks, suggesting the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the modified Rprop algorithm in ensemble formulations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
